options:
require read
require write
existing (implied by require read)
allow multiple (only valid for require read)
directory

valid combos:

single_read: read_only checked,
multi_read
single_write
single_read_write_optional
multi_read_write_optional
single_read_write_required
multi_read_write_required
dir_read
dir_write (is this even needed?)
dir_read_write_optional
dir_read_write_required

single: all
multi: read, read_write_optional, read_write_required

checkbox: blank, checked-gray, blank-gray
blank => any or directory 
checked-gray => existing

scenarios:
any file, possibly creating (rw) (modify or overwrite)
existing file (ro, rw)
directory (ro, rw) (show or hide files)
existing files (ro, rw)

identifiers and titles:
(cs) Create File (AnyFile, rw); overwrite warning
(ws) Create/Modify File (AnyFile, rw)
(ms) Modify File (ExistingFile, rw)
(os) Open File (ExistingFile, ro or rw)
(rs) Read File (ExistingFile, ro)
(mm) Modify Files (ExistingFiles, rw)
(om) Open Files (ExistingFiles, ro or rw)
(rm) Read Files (ExistingFiles, ro)
(md) Modify Directory (Directory, rw)
(od) Open Directory (Directory, ro or rw)
(rd) Read Directory (Directory, ro)

open file (ro) (single,multi)
open file and possibly update it (ro or rw) (single,multi)
open file for input and modification (rw) (single,multi)

checks:
	exists (with different prompts and responses)
(cs) Create File (AnyFile, rw)
	overwrite warning
	writeable
(ws) Create/Modify File (AnyFile, rw)
	overwrite warning (different text)
	writeable
(ms) Modify File (ExistingFile, rw)
	writeable
(os) Open File (ExistingFile, ro or rw)
	readable/writeable
(rs) Read File (ExistingFile, ro)
	readable
(mm) Modify Files (ExistingFiles, rw)
	writeable
(om) Open Files (ExistingFiles, ro or rw)
	readable/writeable
(rm) Read Files (ExistingFiles, ro)
	readable
(md) Modify Directory (Directory, rw)
	writeable
(od) Open Directory (Directory, ro or rw)
	readable/writeable
(rd) Read Directory (Directory, ro)
	readable
